column11: Recommend just keeping several of these on hand and treating them as general supplies, rather than specific to this board.

Recommend just keeping several of these on hand and treating them as general supplies, rather than specific to this board.
These are high current shunts, mainly for use in selecting the BATTERY_+ voltage level (1s or 2s). Other, cheaper shunts will work on the other jumpers.
Only one of these interconnect cables is strictly necessary. But it might be useful to have extras of various sizes.
